{"key":"post-7655953","value":"<?xml version=\"1.0\"?>\n<post>\n<id>7655953</id>\n<content>If the contamination happens before you inoculate, then you're either missing a filter or not sterilizing properly.  Steam for 90 minutes after the steam begins escaping from the lid.  I elevate the jars completely out of the water, so only steam gets on them, but it's important not to start counting the 90 minutes until steam begins to escape from the lid.  This is usually several minutes after the water itself starts boiling.&lt;br /&gt;RR</content>\n<name>RogerRabbit</name>\n<next>7656726</next>\n<prev>7655723</prev>\n<first>7648103</first>\n<last>7658003</last>\n<when>1195517998</when>\n<utime>11/20/07 02:19 AM</utime>\n</post>"}